# stow ignore file -- https://www.gnu.org/software/stow/manual/html_node/Types-And-Syntax-Of-Ignore-Lists.html
#
# With --no-folding (see bootstrap), stow walks into every package subdir
# and links files individually. The invariant this repo relies on is:
# "whatever exists on disk in the package is tracked and meant to be stowed."
# Keeping the repo clean of untracked/gitignored files (via .gitignore and
# `git clean -fdX`) means this ignore file only needs to cover git metadata
# and repo-root files that aren't part of any package.

\.git
\.gitignore
\.gitmodules

^/README.md
^/TMUX.md
^/bootstrap
^/macos
